{"lemma":"رَقَباتُ","slug":"رَقَباتُ","root":"ر.ق.ب","root_slug":"ر-ق-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-ق-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"رَقَبَة","root":"رقب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":9},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n16301","n16306","n16307","n16308"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%8E%D9%82%D9%8E%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"neck"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a slave","tags":["metonymically"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of رَقَبَ (raqaba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of رَقَبَ (raqaba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ra.qa.ba/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n16301","headword_ar":"رَقَبَهُ","root":"rqb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (JK, S, Mgh, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Mgh, Msb,) inf. n. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rqobapN","text_ar":"رقْبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (JK, S, Mgh, K,) or this is a simple subst., (Msb,) and [the inf. n. is]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riqobaAnN","text_ar":"رِقْبَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruquwbN","text_ar":"رُقُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raquwbN","text_ar":"رَقُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqobapN","text_ar":"رَقْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqaAbapN","text_ar":"رَقَابَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He looked, watched,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"waited, for him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it; he awaited,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"expected, him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, A, Mgh, Msb, K;) namely, a man, (JK, A,) or a thing; (S;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"trqbhu","text_ar":"ترقبهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (JK, * S, * A, Msb, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Artqbhu","text_ar":"ارتقبهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, * A, Msb, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rAqbhu","text_ar":"راقبهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muraAqabapN","text_ar":"مُرَاقَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (JK, S, A, Mgh, Msb.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaEada yaroqubu SaAHibahu","text_ar":"قَعَدَ يَرْقُبُ صَاحِبَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sat looking, watching,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"waiting, for his com-"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1133},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"panion;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yarotaqibuhu","text_ar":"يَرْتَقِبُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ka*aA","text_ar":"كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ataraq~abu","text_ar":"اَتَرَقَّبُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I look,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"am looking,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for such a thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaroqubu mawota SaAHibihi","text_ar":"يَرْقُبُ مَوْتَ صَاحِبِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He looks,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the death of his companion"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (JK, S, A, Mgh, Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abiyhi liyarivahu","text_ar":"اَبِيهِ لِيَرِثَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of his father, in order that he may inherit his property"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (A:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"turaAqibu","text_ar":"تُرَاقِبُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mawota baEolihaA","text_ar":"مَوْتَ بَعْلِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She looks,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the death of her husband"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (K, TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liyamuwta fatarivahu","text_ar":"لِيَمُوتَ فَتَرِثَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that he may die and she may inherit his property"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lamo taroqubo qawoliY","text_ar":"لَمْ تَرْقُبْ قَوْلِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [xx. 95], means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And thou didst not wait,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hast not waited, for my saying"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what I should say"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (JK, TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqabahu","text_ar":"رَقَبَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) aor. as above, (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruquwbN","text_ar":"رُقُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He guarded, kept, preserved,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"took care of, it; was mindful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"regardful, of it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K;) namely, a thing; (TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rAqbhu","text_ar":"راقبهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muraAqabapN","text_ar":"مُرَاقَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riqaAbN","text_ar":"رِقَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) [and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"trq~bhu","text_ar":"ترقّبهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":".] You say also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaA A^aroqubu lakumu A@ll~ayolapa","text_ar":"اَنَا اَرْقُبُ لَكُمُ ا@للَّيْلَةَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will guard,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"keep watch, for you to-night."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He regarded it; paid regard,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consideration, to it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd and Jel in ix. 8.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA laka laA taroqubu","text_ar":"مَا لَكَ لَا تَرْقُبُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*im~apa fulaAnK","text_ar":"ذِمَّةَ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What aileth thee that thou wilt not regard the inviolable right"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"due,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of such a one?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A. [This phrase is there mentioned as proper, not tropical.]) ―         -b4-  And (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He feared him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rAqbhu","text_ar":"راقبهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, A, Mgh;) namely, God; (S, Mgh;)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY A^amorihi","text_ar":"فِى اَمْرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in his affair"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S;) because he who fears looks for, or expects, punishment ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaroqubu AlEiqaAba","text_ar":"يَرْقُبُ العِقَابَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"): (A, Mgh:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@ll~`ha","text_ar":"ا@للّٰهَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAqabotu","text_ar":"رَاقَبْتُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I feared the punishment of God."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riqobapN","text_ar":"رِقْبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqaba","text_ar":"رَقَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"app. used intransitively, or perhaps as a simple subst.,] signifies (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fearing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being afraid"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of a person or thing]: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fear:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and also (assumed tropical:)  the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"guarding oneself; being watchful, vigilant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heedful:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"self-guardance;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (K, TA. [See this word below.]) ―         -b5-  And you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAta yaroqubu Aln~ujuwma","text_ar":"بَاتَ يَرْقُبُ النُّجُومَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yuraAqibuhaA","text_ar":"يُرَاقِبُهَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaroEaAhaA","text_ar":"يَرْعَاهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yuraAEiyhaA","text_ar":"يُرَاعِيهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He passed the night watching the stars and waiting for the time when they would disappear"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, TA.) IAar cites the following saying of one describing a travelling-companion of his:"},{"kind":"quote","text":"Aln~ajoma riqaAba AlHuwti ↓ \n      yuraAqibu"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He watches"},{"kind":"text","text":"(↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yarotaqibu","text_ar":"يَرْتَقِبُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the star,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"asterism, with vehement desire"},{"kind":"text","text":"for departure, like"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"watching with"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vehement desire of the fish"},{"kind":"text","text":"for water. (TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqiybN","text_ar":"رَقِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqaba fulaAnFA","text_ar":"رَقَبَ فُلَانًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He put the rope"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a rope"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqabap","text_ar":"رَقَبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"neck,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"base of the hinder part of the neck,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of such a one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqiba","text_ar":"رَقِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [aor."},{"kind":"text","text":",] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqabN","text_ar":"رَقَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) or this is a simple subst., (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, thick in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqabap","text_ar":"رَقَبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"neck,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["JK","S","Mgh","Msb","K","A","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n16306","headword_ar":"رُقْبَةٌ","root":"rqb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A pit made for the purpose of catching the leopard"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: it is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"namir","text_ar":"نَمِر"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zuboyap","text_ar":"زُبْيَة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the lion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, K.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n16307","headword_ar":"رِقْبَةٌ","root":"rqb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see 1, first sentence: ―         -b2-  and again, in the latter half of the paragraph. [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wariva fulaAnN maAlFA Eano riqobapK","text_ar":"وَرِثَ فُلَانٌ مَالًا عَنْ رِقْبَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one inherited property from distant relations; not from his fathers."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wariva Almajoda Eano riqobapK","text_ar":"وَرِثَ المَجْدَ عَنْ رِقْبَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He inherited glory,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nobility, from distant relations:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[it is said of a man] because it is feared that it will not be conceded to him on account of the obscurity of his lineage. (A.) El-Kumeyt says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"kaAna Als~adaY waAln~adaY majodFA wamakorumapF\n                      \n                     \n                        tiloka AlmakaArimu lamo yuwravona Eino riqabi"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The night-dew and the day-dew"},{"kind":"text","text":"that nourished his mental growth"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"were nobility and generous disposition: those generous qualities were not inherited from distant relations:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riqabN","text_ar":"رِقَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riqobapN","text_ar":"رِقْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: i. e., he inherited them from near ancestors. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n16308","headword_ar":"رَقَبَةٌ","root":"rqb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"neck:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"base of the hinder part thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hinder part of the base of the neck:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upper part of the neck:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) pl. [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riqaAbN","text_ar":"رِقَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, Msb, K) and [coll. gen. n.] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqabN","text_ar":"رَقَبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, K) and [pl. of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroqubN","text_ar":"اَرْقُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqabaAtN","text_ar":"رَقَبَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, Msb, K.) ―         -b2-  By a synecdoche, it is applied to (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whole person"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a human being: as in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*anobuhu fiY raqabatihi","text_ar":"ذَنْبُهُ فِى رَقَبَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His sin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crime,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"be on his"},{"kind":"text","text":"own"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"neck;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on himself"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (IAth, TA.) [Hence also] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA AlA^amoru fiY riqaAbikumo","text_ar":"هٰذَا الاَمْرُ فِى رِقَابِكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This affair is upon your own selves"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY raqabatika","text_ar":"فِى رَقَبَتِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon thine own self"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEotaqa A@ll~`hu raqabatahu","text_ar":"اَعْتَقَ ا@للّٰهُ رَقَبَتَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God emancipate him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laka","text_ar":"لَكَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riqaAbuhun~a wamaA Ealayohin~a","text_ar":"رِقَابُهُنَّ وَمَا عَلَيْهِنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in a trad., relating to camels, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They themselves, and the burdens that are upon them, are thine."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And [hence], in another trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lanaA riqaAbu AlA^aroDi","text_ar":"لَنَا رِقَابُ الاَرْضِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"To us belongs the land itself."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  Hence also, i. e. by a synecdoche, (IAth, Mgh, TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A slave,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, IAth, Mgh, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"male"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a captive:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riqaAbN","text_ar":"رِقَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEotaqa raqabapF","text_ar":"اَعْتَقَ رَقَبَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He emancipated a slave, male"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fak~a raqabapF","text_ar":"فَكَّ رَقَبَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He released a slave,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a captive."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~iqaAb","text_ar":"الرِّقَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the Kur ix. 60 means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Those slaves who have contracted with their owners for their freedom."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, Mgh, Msb, TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riqaAbu AlmazaAwidi","text_ar":"رِقَابُ المَزَاوِدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  [lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The necks of provision-bags"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is a nickname which was applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eajam","text_ar":"عَجَم"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Persians,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foreigners"},{"kind":"text","text":"in general]; because they were red; (S, A;) or because of the length of their necks; (El-Karáfee, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zwd","text_ar":"زود"},{"kind":"text","text":";) or rather because of the thickness thereof, as though they were full. (MF in that art.)"}],"source_refs":["A","K","JK","S","TA","Msb","IAar","IAth","Mgh"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}